main event: A luminous, round object was observed hovering in the sky and moving erratically from side to side before disappearing.
interesting points: The object was observed for 40-45 minutes.
The witnesses did not believe the object was an aircraft.
The report was unable to explain the nature or origin of the object.
The report listed the object as a 'possible astronomical' or 'possible aircraft' sighting, but ultimately concluded it was 'unidentified'.
The report mentions a second sighting by the crew of the SS Flying A California, with the object seen for about 30 minutes and reaching a maximum altitude of 60.
